  <h6>1. Create a Facebook App</h6>
  <p>
    Create a new Facebook App and Page or use existing ones. Go to the App Dashboard and under Product Settings click "Add Product" and select "Messenger."
  </p>
  <div class="tuto">
   <%= image_tag "tutorial_1.png", width: "800" %>
 </div>

 <h6>2. Setup Webhook</h6>

 <div class="tuto">
   <p>In the Webhooks section, click "Setup Webhooks."<p>
     <%= image_tag "tutorial_2.png", width: "800" %>
   </div>



   <div class="tuto">
     <%= image_tag "tutorial_3.png", width: "800" %>
     <br><br><br>
     <p>Paste this in the URL section </p> <h5>https://localhost:3000.com//bots/<%= @bot.id %>/webhook</h5>
     <br><br><br>
     <p> Paste this in the Verify Token <h5><%= @bot.token %></h5> </p> <br>
     <p>Select message_deliveries, messages, messaging_optins, and messaging_postbacks under Subscription Fields.</p>
   </div>

   <h6> 3. Get a Page Access Token</h6>

   <p>Stick your Page Access Token below</p>

   <%= simple_form_for(@bot) do |f| %>
   <%= f.error_notification %>

   <%= f.input :page_access_token %>
   <%= f.button :submit, :class => 'btn btn-primary' %>
   <% end %>

   <h6>4. Subscribe the App to the Page</h6>

 </div>
</div>



